documentation.text:
@dev Sets the color for all `tokenIds`.  `colors` will be updated for `tokenIds` with the same index.
 Setting the color is actually just emitting an event.
 For example tokenIds=[10,50] and colors=[x,y] would emit events 
 ColorBytesUpdated(10, <msg.sender>, x) and ColorBytesUpdated(50, <msg.sender>, y)
 Requires tokenIds and colors to be the same length.

documentation.text:
@dev Sets the `color` for `tokenId`
 Setting the color is actually just emitting an event.
 Does a sanity check to ensure people aren't uploading full size images or other large data.
 Full validation of the color byte array is handled off chain to ensure it is a png, jpg, or gif.
 Emits a {ColorBytesUpdated} event

devdoc.details: ERC721, Non-Fungible Token, implementation.  There are 7056 available NFTs.  Includes functionality to mint new tiles as well as to update the color of the tile.

ColorBytesUpdated(uint256,address,bytes).details: Emitted when `owner` changes the `tokenId` color to `updatedColor`.

getOwner(uint256).details: Returns the owner of the tile, or the empty address if no owner exists or out of range.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

ownerOf(uint256).details: Reimplements ownerOf to default the owner to the contract creator.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setColorBytes(uint256,bytes).details: Sets the `color` for `tokenId` Setting the color is actually just emitting an event. Does a sanity check to ensure people aren't uploading full size images or other large data. Full validation of the color byte array is handled off chain to ensure it is a png, jpg, or gif. Emits a {ColorBytesUpdated} event

setColorBytesBulk(uint256[],bytes[]).details: Sets the color for all `tokenIds`.  `colors` will be updated for `tokenIds` with the same index. Setting the color is actually just emitting an event. For example tokenIds=[10,50] and colors=[x,y] would emit events  ColorBytesUpdated(10, <msg.sender>, x) and ColorBytesUpdated(50, <msg.sender>, y) Requires tokenIds and colors to be the same length.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
